pullRequest.title: CLDR-14163 Add missing character to parseLenients
pullRequest.bodyText:
This should fix the failing ICU exhaustive test.
I only updated these sets in the root.  I did not touch any that might exist in child locales.
Checklist

 Issue filed: https://unicode-org.atlassian.net/browse/CLDR-14163
 Updated PR title and link in previous line to include Issue number

nodes.bodyText: Adding OL CHIKI PHAARKAA is very strange; it is a modifier letter, not a math symbol, general symbol or punctuation. We don't want to add arbitrary confusables. I think the change should be in ICU.
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -67,13 +67,13 @@ for derived annotations.
 			<parseLenient sample="₹">[₨₹{Rp}{Rs}]</parseLenient>
 		</parseLenients>
 		<parseLenients scope="number" level="lenient">
-			<parseLenient sample="-">[\-‐‒–⁻₋−➖﹣－]</parseLenient>
-			<parseLenient sample=",">[,،٫、︐︑﹐﹑，､]</parseLenient>
+			<parseLenient sample="-">[\-ᱼ‐‒–⁻₋−➖﹣－]</parseLenient>

nodes.bodyText:
See comment below.
U+1C79 | OL CHIKI GAAHLAA TTUDDAAG is a modifier letter. Suggest removing from ICU's test.
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@ for derived annotations.
 			<parseLenient sample=":">[\:∶︓﹕：]</parseLenient>
 		</parseLenients>
 		<parseLenients scope="general" level="lenient">
-			<parseLenient sample=".">[.․。︒﹒．｡]</parseLenient>
+			<parseLenient sample=".">[.ᱹ․。︒﹒．｡]</parseLenient>

nodes.bodyText: This REVERSED COMMA looks ok (unlikely to ever happen) but it is a punctuation character at least.

nodes.bodyText:
So we could take this but not the others, and make 2 changes in ICU.
Or just make 3 changes in ICU.
